name: English Australian (Fluorite & Black Opal)
description:
The idea of this work addresses the natural resources extracted from mineral-rich countries and the assignment of more rights and privileges to cross borders than some people in minority, marginalized, and vulnerable communities.

It is also a reflection of the physical traits from two races recognizable and perpetually on display in one being. These visual signifiers of race, in some cases, reinforce essentialist, either/or thinking and harmful stereotypes, which can dictate who does or does not have the access to travel freely around the world.
